>
>VISA's response is to issue 30,000 watermark cards to customers in Northampton,
>England, in a field trial. These cards have a unique serial number embedded in
>the strip; it is high-coercivity and laterally polarised in order to be both
>onvisible to (and unalterable by) normal terminals. Safeways, a local 
>supermarket chain, is installing readers which check these numbers (there is a
>crypto checksum of the number and the normal card data on the mag strip).
>
>If anybody gets hold of one of these, then I know a magnetics expert who would 
>very much like to borrow it for a few days of tests! I understand a similar
>system is used in Sweden; anybody there care to donate an expired card in order
>to further the cause of scientific research?

